  "local_port": 46374,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What social media etiquette do we often forget?",
  "response": "Social media etiquette is a set of guidelines that help ensure respectful, positive interactions online. While there are many rules to keep in mind, here are some key aspects of social media etiquette that people often forget:\n\n1. **Think Before You Post**: One of the most common mistakes is posting impulsively. Before sharing something, consider its potential impact on your personal and professional life. Ask yourself if the content is appropriate and whether it could be misinterpreted.\n\n2. **Respect Privacy**: Don't share personal information about others without their consent. This includes tagging people in photos or mentioning them in posts without their permission.\n\n3. **Avoid Over-sharing**: While it's tempting to share every detail of your life, remember that not everything needs to be public. Oversharing can lead to information fatigue and may make others uncomfortable.\n\n4. **Engage Positively**: Social media is a platform for interaction. Engage with others respectfully and constructively. Avoid negative comments, online arguments, and inflammatory posts.\n\n5. **Give Credit Where It's Due**: If you share content that isn't yours, always give credit to the original creator. This includes using hashtags like #Repost or mentioning the original source.\n\n6. **Mind Your Hashtags**: Use hashtags sparingly and relevantly. Overusing hashtags can make your post look spammy and detract from your message.\n\n7. **Be Mindful of Timing**: Don't post at inappropriate times, such as during tragic events or holidays, unless your message is relevant and sensitive to the context.\n\n8. **Edit Before You Post**: Always review your posts for spelling and grammar errors. A well-crafted post reflects positively on you and makes your message clearer.\n\n9. **Respect Diverse Opinions**: Social media connects people from various backgrounds. Be open to different viewpoints and engage in discussions respectfully, even if you disagree.\n\n10. **Acknowledge and Apologize for Mistakes**: If you post something that offends or misleads others, acknowledge your mistake and apologize promptly. This shows maturity and helps maintain your online reputation.\n\nBy keeping these guidelines in mind, you can navigate social media more effectively and maintain positive relationships online.",
